This slices using `strings.Index(method, \".\")` without guarding against `-1`. If a request arrives with an unexpected/malformed `CtxAPINameKey` value (missing a `.`), this will panic. Add an index check and return a non-retriable error when the delimiter is missing.
```suggestion
	idx := strings.Index(method, ".")
	if idx == -1 {
		return nil, nonRetriableError{fmt.Errorf("unable to dispatch request, malformed CtxAPINameKey value %q", method)}
	}
	client := method[:idx]
```

